The paper proposes a model-based reinforcement learning approach for sequence generation, which involves training a guider network to provide intermediate rewards for generator optimization. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, given the focus on sequence generation and language modeling, cs.LG and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories.
